<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.001J56.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Jiménez</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I acknowledge with profound thanks your felicitations on the occasion of
                            the inauguration of my administration and reciprocate your wishes for
                            the Republic by formulating a very sincere one for the great American
                            people and X our Excellency’s personal happiness.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan I. Jiménez</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>